seams.what_it_does:
The flywheel's ONLY markdown renderer. `bodies.append(f"## {sr.title}

{sr.verified_text}")` for each non-dropped section; `sections_concat = "

".join(bodies)`; optional `## Limitations`; a `## References` list built by string concat; `final_report = f"# {title}

{intro}

{sections_concat}{biblio_section}"` written to report.md. That is the entire document grammar: H1, a fixed intro paragraph, a flat list of H2s each followed by one opaque text blob, H2 References. It never reads multi.trial_summary_table_text, multi.trial_timeline_text, multi.m50_per_trial_subsections_text, or multi.analyst_synthesis_text — all of which the generator computes and returns.

